<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id050f690d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s81p"><num value="81p">§ 81p.</num><heading> Accounts and recordkeeping</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id050f690e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s81p/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Manner of keeping accounts</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The form and manner of keeping the accounts of each zone shall be prescribed by the Board.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id050f690f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s81p/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Annual report by grantee</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each grantee shall make to the Board annually, and at such other times as it may prescribe, reports on zone operations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id050f6910-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s81p/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Report to Congress</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Board shall make a report to Congress annually containing a summary of zone operations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id050f6911-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/act/1934-06-18/ch590/s16">June 18, 1934, ch. 590, § 16</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/48/1002">48 Stat. 1002</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/96/609/tII/s204">Pub. L. 96–609, title II, § 204</ref>, <date date="1980-12-28">Dec. 28, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/3561">94 Stat. 3561</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/386/tII/s203/b">Pub. L. 99–386, title II, § 203(b)</ref>, <date date="1986-08-22">Aug. 22, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/823">100 Stat. 823</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id050f6912-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id050f6913-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id050f6914-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1986—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/99/386/s203/b/1">Pub. L. 99–386, § 203(b)(1)</ref>, substituted “reports on zone operations” for “reports containing a full statement of all the operations, receipts, and expenditures, and such other information as the Board may require”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Subsec. (c). <ref href="/us/pl/99/386/s203/b/2">Pub. L. 99–386, § 203(b)(2)</ref>, added subsec. (c) and struck out former subsec. (c) which required the Board to make an annual report to Congress containing a summary of the operation and fiscal condition of each zone, and transmit copies of the annual report of each grantee.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1980—Subsec. (c). <ref href="/us/pl/96/609">Pub. L. 96–609</ref> substituted “by April 1 of each year” for “on the first day of each regular session”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
